title: Vulpix/Ninetales
body:
To start off, for my team, the character that is me is named Meghan, because that is my name and this is literally a self insert that i’ve been developing and re-imagining and shaping ever since i was like 5 to who i am, how i see myself, and how i WANT to be

so anyway, the story starts off with a three year old Meghan, a stubborn, pokemon loving kid runs off into the forest behind her house one day, wanting to be on an adventure just like her big brother (who is at this point in time 12)

in her day of exploring, she comes across two eggs that have been abandoned, one red and one blue, no parent in sight and they’re not even in real nests or anything

she first finds the red one, and then finds the blue one a bit later in the day, she wraps them up in her security blanket that she took with her, and then takes them home

Her parents are very displeased with her running off, and very unwilling to let her keep the eggs, but what else are they going to do? Abandon them?

A couple of days later, one of the eggs hatch and it’s a baby Vulpix! Technically Meghan’s first pokemon, even though she got both of the eggs at close to the same time.

Meghan immediately falls in love with her and shows her parents, who are very uneasy about letting this three year old have a pokemon, but decide that maybe it would be good for her and it’s not like she’s actually a trainer now right? haha ha

Vulpix is pretty no-nonsense, doesn’t take crap from anybody, calm, supportive, gentle and kindhearted, and only when pushed to the limit, hot-headed. She loves battling and knows that she is strong, and gets irritated if anyone tries to say otherwise

In fact, throughout their adventures, even though Meghan got a fire stone not super long after she got vulpix, Vulpix didn’t want to evolve until she had proven that she was good enough, and she was very strict on herself to prove herself worthy of evolving, it actually took her YEARS before she decided she was worthy enough of Meghan’s fire stone and evolved when Meghan was 12

Ability: Drought

Moves (as of now): Flamethrower, Solar Beam, Extrasensory, Flare Blitz

Also sometimes knows/has known: Quick Attack, Hex, Energy Ball, Hidden Power, Flame Charge

summary: The battlefield is designed to be inconvenient to as many types as possible. The whole thing is just one big pool, with a few...
body:
The battlefield is designed to be inconvenient to as many types as possible. The whole thing is just one big pool, with a few rocks poking out of the water here and there to give challengers somewhere to stand. Misty is impatiently waiting at the other end with one hand on her hip and the other tossing a Pokeball up and down. She’s wearing a bikini, and I’m not sure if it’s because she’s actually been swimming in the battlefield-pool or if she just wants more people to tune in to her matches on the Battle Network.


Tessa takes on Misty in Chapter 11 of The Scientist!
